verbs.description: overdare (third-person singular simple present overdares, present participle overdaring, simple past and past participle overdared)

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To dare too much or rashly; to be too daring.
examples: When one so great has spoken of love to one
So little as I, though to deny him love,
What can he but hold out beseeching hands,
Then let them fall beside him, knowing how greatly
